    "We refer to P G as a motif counting since, when applied to the vanilla adjacency matrix Y *, the polynomial P G (Y *) merely counts the occurence in Y * of the motif G \"attached\" at i and j.",
    "Our goal is to prove Conjecture 1.4 of [CGV25] that predicts that community recovery is possible above the threshold (2) through the enumeration of specific motifs satisfying certain structural properties.",
